      "writtenOn": "2017-10-06T04:48:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i re-read this a couple of times and this sentence is still unclear to me.\n\nalso, with these changes, this code no longer handles out-of-order delivery of build messages for the same revision, e.g. a build for commit X failed. We retried the build on the same commit X (say because it was a flake and there were no new commits) and got a green build.\n\nFWIU we want the order of statuses to be 1) commit time, then 2) build time",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 96,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "fdf8e76dd6d7e4ae6f5aa5ddb03d1e2b5371c154",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
